(115, 33, 'HOD reviewed', 'yearly', 'Bsc Agroforestry and Rural Development.', 'Plantation Manager', '4', '4', NULL, '4', '01/01/2022 - 11/11/2022', 'Employee: Comments\r\n\r\nThe year has been of corrections to ensure all aspects of the project/s go on well as planned going forward. A lot of training has been received all aligned to the companyâ€™s mission and vision and a lot of explanations and elaborations done e.g., why we need to always have the correct stock figures from the nursery to the plantation. The importance of communication and doing things right the first time has also been elaborated and insisted on the team.\r\n\r\nThis I can attest has had a positive effect to me and the team and we are ready to take on the coming yearâ€™s targets while maintaining and improving systems set in place to achieve the companyâ€™s objectives. \r\n\r\nSupervisor: Comments\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\nHOD: Comments\r\n\r\nThere have been changes over the months in the objectives and the focus was on maintenance of the plantations, tree stock verification, and correction of all areas we have had challenges in. This required that plans are made for the maintenance activities, the teams being supervised are checked, guided accordingly, and made to understand the importance of the activities being carried out and how all these are aligned with the company\'s vision, mission, and short term objectives. Some of these activities were done well like stock verification in Kiambere, taking charge in the absence of a supervisor in Kiambere, improved pruning and cleaning by the teams involved. Some areas that had gaps but were addressed later in the year included the importance of tree counting and how all the activities we do are linked to the company\'s vision and mission. This however is something he must continuously address to his team. Other areas that need to be improved upon are as follows:\r\n\r\n1. Managing of plans:- It is not enough to make a plan but they must be constantly followed up and implemented. \r\n\r\n2. Being objective:- Focus should be on achieving the set objectives. Being nice or lenient to your team cannot help him in achieving the agreed-upon objectives. He should spend less time in back and forth explanations with his team that lead to delays in some instances and indecisiveness. Should focus on facts.\r\n\r\n3. He needs to work towards doing more within his capacity so that he can grow as a manager. He should not limit himself to simply just taking instructions, , relaying information or simply following up with issues. At his level, he should put more initiative in thinking or motivating his teams of solutions to improve his domain. \r\n\r\n4. Communication has also been an issue, however, this has been emphasized largely this year but should be something that he constantly addresses.\r\n\r\n5. Delegating of tasks should be improved because this is one of the ways he can help his team grow in capacity.', '2022-11-07 16:23:15', '2022-11-22 10:19:43'),
(116, 149, 'completed', 'yearly', 'Bachelor of Community forestry and Master of science in Environment and Natural resource management', 'Country Representative-UG', '10.8', '131', NULL, NULL, '11/07/2022 - 11/07/2022', 'last appraised in 2020: In this year of Covid-19 restrictions, Diana has responded well to on-line cooperation through Zoom meetings and other internet applications like Telegram. She has managed to maintain and expand slightly her subscription base and even got more articles, despite the circumstances.\r\nShe has however to continue to work on her editing skills including English language and be careful and not sloppy in her editing. But this has been taken care of in her training and development plan. Next year, she really has to do more field visits, to Dokolo, Kenya and South Africa, to upgrade her understanding of modern forestry. \r\nShe is instrumental in  maintaining a lively group of eminent forestry specialists in the Editorial Committee, and surely will increase her subscription database when the magazine goes digital. She made a good start with Rotary, as a basis for more visits next year, again with the objective of increasing the subscription base.', '2022-11-07 17:55:14', '2022-11-08 16:28:46'),
