(166, 44, 'HOD reviewed', 'yearly', 'Kenya Certificate of Secondary Education', 'Plantation Maintenance', '5', '68', 33, '4', '10/11/2021 - 11/10/2022', 'Employee: Comments\r\n\r\nFirst I have to thank the company for this far . Indeed this company has enabled me to achieve a lot in my personal daily activities and even during this covid outbreak most companies laid off workers but we have been at work all through. I am committed towards my work and I will always strive towards achieving my assigned duties as already agreed upon by the supervisor.\r\n\r\nLastly I would request the management team to consider making value of the trees which we do record as dead and windthrows from different compartments instead of letting them rot in the plantation.\r\n\r\nSupervisor: Comments\r\n\r\nThe employee has been committed to his work for the time I have known him. He is well conversant with the whole compartments and has been useful for the interns currently in doing tree measurement. He is flexible and after training can do any chores required. \r\n\r\nHOD: Comments\r\n\r\nJosphat has shown that he has immense knowledge of the Kiambere plantation and knows all the compartments by heart. However being part of the tree counting team, it must be noted that we got wrong figures at the beginning of the year due to incomplete counting and non-communication about areas that need to be cleaned before the tree counting is done.', '2022-11-10 15:24:10', '2022-11-12 16:10:01'),
