(169, 56, 'HOD reviewed', 'yearly', 'Primary level', 'Plantation Maintenance Staff Kiambere', '7', '68', 33, '4', '10/11/2022 - 11/10/2022', 'Employee: Comments\r\n\r\nFirst I have to thank the company for this far . Indeed this company has enabled me to achieve a lot in my personal daily activities and even during this covid outbreak most companies laid off workers but we have been at work all through. I am committed towards my work and I will always strive towards achieving my assigned duties as already agreed upon by the supervisor.\r\n\r\nSupervisor: Comments\r\n\r\nThe employee has been resourceful in the plantation activities. He has specifically taken part in tree marking of the years being that he was there from the time of establishments. He has helped other workers in getting to know the whole plantation.\r\n\r\nHOD: Comments\r\n\r\nHe has acquired various skills apart from maintenance activities. Efforts by HR in explaining issues have clearly had a positive effect and he now sees the company in a positive light. He clearly shows concern about the plantation. He however was still part of the PMF team that did not provide the correct figures at the beginning of the year. It should also be noted that it is ok to pray but even prayers have their place and time on Sundays.', '2022-11-10 17:25:08', '2022-11-11 18:48:15'),
(170, 119, 'HOD reviewed', 'yearly', 'Bsc in Forestry', 'Site Manager Plantation Nyongoro', '3.5', '33', 33, '4', '01/01/2022 - 12/31/2022', 'Employee: Comments\r\n\r\nThe discussion was detailed and informative in terms of pointing out areas to improve on in order to achieve impressive results. \r\n\r\nSupervisor: Comments\r\n\r\nFor the year, Stephen concentrated on maintenance and plantation stock verification exercise. From this exercise he has been able to streamline his team to be more accountable about the figures of all activities they undertake and of the stocks. Mortality was still a problem in the  plantation due to different causes including buffaloes damage. However, going forward it is expected that the team will work towards zero mortality and some measures are already being put in  place such an electric fence round the plantation. \r\n\r\nHe is also expected to make better plans based on the reality on the ground and have periodic checks (daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly and yearly) to ensure the company meets the sites objectives thereby achieving its mission and vision. \r\n\r\nHOD: Comments\r\n\r\nStephen has shown great technical skills in plantation forestry by managing to learn fast and adapting on the job. He has been able to manage people in a difficult environment with all kinds of challenges from the community and the wild animals. This is commendable. However, these qualities should now be channeled into giving the desired results of zero mortality in the plantation. He, therefore, needs to improve in the following areas:\r\n\r\n1. Planning and continuous monitoring. Managing a plantation is not just about field work, but also thorough planning and continuous checks to ensure the activities are implemented and correctly.\r\n\r\n2. Be more open to criticism and take it positively as an opportunity for improvement.\r\n\r\n3. Communication\r\n\r\n4. Be tougher with your team, pointing out their mistakes and punishing these mistakes as per the HR policy rather than trying to be nice to them or protecting them and ending up taking blame for other peoples mistakes.', '2022-11-10 17:54:56', '2022-11-14 15:14:55'),
