(216, 25, 'HOD reviewed', 'yearly', 'MSc Agroforestry', 'Site Nursery Manager', '3', '3', NULL, '4', '01/01/2022 - 11/17/2022', 'By being the site manager for the Dokolo project, Charles has in his hands a great opportunity for growth. There have been massive improvements in handling administrative duties in relation to farmer database. However, for him to successfully manage and implement the project, improvements must suffice in the following areas:\r\n\r\n1. Leadership:- he must lead by example, be brave enough to check his people all times they go wrong, stop being lenient and focus on getting results, must be able to embrace responsibility and inspire his team to get the desired results. \r\n\r\n2. Planning and followup/checking:- must learn to follow through with agreed-upon plans and continuously check his team and continuously communicate any changes.\r\n\r\n3. Communication:- there seemed to be a continuous breakdown in communication that led to the team in Dokolo doing various actions contrary to instructions.', '2022-11-17 14:16:13', '2022-11-22 10:00:51'),
