(168, 41, 128, '<div style=\"border-width: 1pt; border-color: windowtext; border-image: initial; padding: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border-width: 1pt; border-color: windowtext; border-image: initial; padding: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Good coordination, guidance and encouragement<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border: none; padding: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>', '<p>Adopting timely communication</p>', '<p>Sharing resources that are required my department</p>', '<p>to bridge the communication gap. for example if i send an email to the procurement officer with other people in copy like OP,AM and accountant regarding an assignment to be done in the same day, if the PO is on leave the next responsible person should be able to reply and inform me that she is not around or send the documents i requested than leaving me to wait in silence when am not going to be helped. also we can introduce a system of keeping me in copy when people i work with are going on leave.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-11-11 19:11:47', '2022-11-11 19:11:47'),
