(86, 119, 76, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Implement,\r\nSupervise, and control all forestry activities in the Nyongoro nursery\r\naccording to the planning and budget. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Timely\r\nreporting of all activities on site<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Developing\r\nand implementation of approved workplans.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Management\r\nof Human resource on site according to company policies. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->5.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Represent\r\nthe company as required <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->6.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Ensure\r\nthat the health and safety guidelines are implemented. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->7.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Give\r\nshort training sessions to workers on specific subjects <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->8.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Permanent\r\nevaluation of staff performance. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->9.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Make\r\nsuggestions for continuous improvement of all operations on site and encourage\r\nall workers to do the same.</p>', '<p>None</p>', '<p>From roles assigned as indicated in 1(a) dedicates me fully on implementing activities to achieve the company objectives which directly represent the mission and vision of the company through planting and maintaining of trees to the satisfaction of all stakeholders.</p>', '<p>1. Carrying out forest inventory to obtain correct stock in the plantations.</p><p>2. Expansion of M&amp;E department i.e having officer on site for immediate checks in case of arising challenges.</p><p>3. Implementing of measures for preventing spreading of Covid-19 and general hygiene on site by constructing PPE store &amp; toilets.</p><p>4. Embracing technology on procurement and logistical process thus help in reduced paper work ( IPRs, CARs, ticketingbgf etc)</p><p>5. Efforts made on plantation maintenance activities i.e increased mechanizations, installation of electric fence and budget availability for silvicultural treatments.</p>', '<p>Capacity building on advanced forestry technologies through trainings and short courses i.e on forest inventory and forest harvesting.</p>', '<p>Psychological well being of workers due to economy inflation, hunger and drought . This affects work output since staffs are not well settled. There has been frequent absenteeism related to this.&nbsp;</p><p>Tree mortality in the plantation due to wild animals (buffaloes) and disturbances from pastoralists, squatters and arsonists.</p>', '<p>1. Have a long term forestry management plan.</p><p>2. Do research on the timber quality in order to be aware of company assets in terms of quality timber in volumes.</p><p>3. Purchase of advanced forestry measurement tools ( for tree total height, crown diameter, girth and bole height)</p><p><br></p>', '2021-11-11 09:58:16', '2022-05-20 16:23:48'),
(87, 123, 78, '<p><p>1.Supervising Tractor Drivers, Site Mechanic, Security Guards &amp; Heavy Equipment Operators on site.</p><p>2.Project management at Site Level.</p><p>3.Overseeing the Implementation of approved company policies and procedures.</p><p>4. Site Tasks Planning and Implementation.</p>5. Operational Stock Management on Site<br></p><p>6.Implementation, monitoring and measuring of approved procedures and work instructions on site.</p><p>7.Establishing and follow up of operational budget on site.</p><p>8.Maintenance of plant machinery.</p><p>9.Follow up on the overall performance of the machines and ensuring that the machines are always at work.</p><p>10.In charge of operational purchases on site with strict adherence to approved procedures.</p><p>11.Daily follow up of operations onsite including issues related to the H&amp;S of workers.</p><p>12.Offer Logistics support to CSR&nbsp; activities related to BGF.<br></p>', '<p>1.Drone Piloting.</p><p>2.GIS and Remote Sensing Analysis of the Forest Management Unit.<br></p>', '<p>Vision: By implementing and adhering to the approved company policies e.g. The Anti-Corruption and Bribery policy. </p><p>Mission: Ensure that the human workforce on site and the plant machinery are always in good state to perform their duties optimally of planting, maintaining and protecting trees.<br></p>', '<p>1. Successfully attending the drone training and acquiring an RPL License from KCAA.</p><p>2. Managing &amp; Coordinating the installation of the Electric &amp; Nursery Fence at Site-Level.</p><p>3. Construction of the PPE-Store.</p><p>4. Coordinating the repairs of KTCB 563N and 530T at Site Level.</p><p>5. Coordinating the repairs of LGP at site level.</p>', '<p>1. Additional Human Workforce: Store-Keeper; At the moment the SLO is the only one in charge of operations on site \r\nand supervision of vital activities that form the back born of all \r\nactivities &amp; Plumber. </p><p><br></p>', '<p>1. Delayed deliveries from suppliers. E.g. FMD. The supplier is yet to deliver parts (Steering Unions &amp; Steering Cylinder) that could have fixed a long time ago on KTCB 154X &amp; KTCB 356V.</p><p>2. Movement of Supplies from WITU &amp; Mpeketoni to Site. <br></p>', '<p>1. Allocation of means of transport E.g. A Pick-Up.</p>', '2021-11-11 10:43:05', '2022-05-20 16:23:49'),
(88, 37, 79, '<p>1. Having all the accounts documents processed on time</p><p>2. Having the suppliers paid timely.</p><p>3. Having accounts reconciliations done every month.</p><p>4. Ensuring that casual workers are paid every week.</p>', '<p>Document control</p>', '<p>1. Ensuring timely availing of cash and accountability&nbsp;</p><p>2. Ensuring smooth external and internal relations with suppliers.</p>', '<p>Having an up to date financial accounts.</p>', '<p>1. Getting documents to be processed on time.</p>', 'Delayed submission of original documents to accounts office, which leads to duplication when originals are later submitted.', '<p>To receive documents on time (by the end of every Tuesday) from all departments, process and post them on time. This will reduce accumulation of work load and will ensure smooth operation in accounts</p>', '2021-11-11 12:27:32', '2022-05-20 16:21:45'),
(89, 33, 80, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Responsible\r\nfor the budgeting and planning related to plantations according to the company\r\npolicies.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Checking\r\nwork plans, uploading plans for execution on site and monitoring the results.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Regularly\r\nreview if plans have been implemented and continuous follow up.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .25in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\">4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs