(93, 93, 4, '<p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 150%;\">Execute all\r\nplantation Establishment activities according to approved plans</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 150%;\">Manage all raw\r\nrecords related to the plantation establishment</span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;line-height:150%\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 150%;\">Training of\r\nworkers as prescribed in the work instructions for all forestry establishment\r\nactivities</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%\">4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 150%;\">Uphold companyâ€™s\r\npolicies and procedures that relate to forestry activities i.e. achieving the\r\nset task rates, ensuring workers follow set procedures to the latter</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%\">5.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 150%;\">Propose plans for\r\nPlantation establishment Staff and manage them.</span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;line-height:150%\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoBodyText\" style=\"margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%\">6.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; line-height: 150%;\">Propose\r\nimprovement</span></p>', '<p>1. Handling of plantation maintenance activities.</p>', '<p>Contributing to the reduction of poverty and corruption through planting and maintenance of trees which increases chances of employment to the unemployed local communities. Working in transparency, accountability and equity to the company contribute in the expansion of the company and ability to plant and maintain many trees as people on earth.</p>', '<p>1. Excellent maintenance of the plantation through proper mechanization of silvicultural practices such as pruning and cleaning.</p><p>2. Correct data in regards to biological stock of the plantation has been achieved.</p><p>3. Excellent effort to provide all workers with health and safety requirements and ensuring compliance while at work place.</p>', '<p>1. Provide training on remote sensing and soil mapping will help in identifying suitable plantable areas, provide correct data for analysis and decision making by the management.</p>', '<p>1. Continous damages of trees by wildlife and vandalism of company properties by unauthorized pastoralists in the plantation.</p><p>2. Lack of means of transport to workers from site to the respective areas of work in the plantation.</p><p>3. Salary and wages deductions for workers.</p>', '<p>1. Make more effort on electric fence maintenance to ensure no more damages by wild animals.</p><p>2. Provide insentive i.e monthly bonuses to workers who have done excellent job.</p><p>3. Areas of electric fence with rampant damages by wild animals to be reinforced by digging shallow trenches to further control the menace.</p>', '2021-11-12 09:53:50', '2022-05-20 16:23:44'),
(94, 4, 83, '<p>Responsible for the Forestry Department, planning, ensuring plans are approved timely and the implementation of approved forestry plans. The Implementation includes managing the resources.</p>', '<p>No special task or as they come&nbsp;</p>', '<p>The ultimate goal for the implementation of the foresty plans is that all the trees planted survive. The implementation process should be done in a cost-effective and efficient way. There should also be impact especially in the farmers program of which is created by improving the farmers livilhoods (IGAs). This is directly related to the company\'s mission and the vision.&nbsp;</p>', 'Nothing much has happened this year with regards to production, planting or recruiting farmers these usually will define benchmarks for success in my capacity. In spite of this, the change in strategy to concentrate on finding the truth and correcting all the things that are not ok have presented me an opportunity to better understand the projects being managed. This has given me more insight and understanding of the people i manage, the resources and i believe that i am now in a better position to implement the forestry projects.', '<p>1. Better planning:- Plans that are well thought out based on the reality on the ground, the plans must have monitoring plans that are dynamic. Shorter reaction times to monitor the implementation of these plans for faster decision-making.</p><p>2. More time in training the staff in forestry.</p><p><br></p>', '<p>1. Dishonest staff due to lack of effective supervision and checks</p><p><br></p>', '<p>N/A</p>', '2021-11-12 10:33:04', '2022-05-20 16:21:39'),
