(198, 4, 197, '<p>1.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">Involved in short-term and long-term planning for the forestry department</span></p><p>2. Ensure that the day-to-day forestry activities are done according to approved plans and smoothly</p><p>3. Part of the management team</p><p>4. Coordinating and implementing FCS activities&nbsp;</p><p>5. Implement communication policies through dedicated meetings with forestry staff.</p><p>6. Implementing Human resource policies within the forestry department.&nbsp;</p><p>7. Managing all forestry staff&nbsp;</p><p>All of the above is aimed at ensuring that we are in line with the company\'s mission and vision.</p><p><br></p>', '<p>None</p>', '<p>The vision and mission of the company are unique and bold, especially in the African setting where deforestation is massive, and there are high poverty and corruption levels. I believe that the vision and mission are achievable and will make a great impact on the livelihood of the communities in which we work.</p>', '<p>1. Milestones in FCS implementation.</p><p>2. Improved tools for planning within the department.</p>', '<p>1. More field visits</p><p>2. Faster development of digital tools for use by forestry for managing farmers and plantations.</p>', '<p>1. Decreasing number of staff that need to be replaced and additional staff. This led to the non-achievement of targets in maintenance and group formation.&nbsp;</p><p>2. Delays in completion of farmers\' program applications.</p><p>3. Lack of staff motivation, commitment, and discipline.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>1. Timely Recruitment of staff.</p><p>2. More emphasis on training and measurement.</p><p>3. Continue with the internship program.</p><p>4. Continuous improvement in digital management tools.</p><p><br></p>', '2022-11-14 16:15:25', '2022-11-14 16:15:25');
