(129, 46, '2)	To ensure zero mortality within Kiambere during seedling production.', 'Not Achieved', 'During the production we use different casuals who might not be well conversant with the activities. I would suggest a team for every activity to be identified and specialize in one line like watering, pricking, e.t.c.\r\n\r\nThe second reason is the soil type being used in seedling production. Soil test needs to be done before taking any soil for potting.\r\n\r\nThe season of planting should be considered and the best time during dry and sunny period. This years production commence during cold season and this affected the survival of the seedlings.\r\n\r\nThe hygiene for the nursery area should be considered and maintained, no food stuff to be allowed in the nursery area.', 'However the employee did not take part in the production process but identified some gaps which will be worked on in the next production process.', '2021-11-10 05:40:16', '2021-11-10 05:40:16'),
(130, 46, '3)	To maintain existing areas of the plantation by implementing silvicultural practices e.g. Pruning, Cleaning and weeding', 'Achieved', 'Maintenance activities in the plantation has been well done, however for pruning, most trees are above five years and we might require long ladders to continue with pruning in such areas.', 'The employee is well trained in these silvicultural activities especially pruning and could help in translations to the local dialect during trainings.', '2021-11-10 05:40:16', '2021-11-10 05:40:16'),
(131, 46, '4)	Present correct daily results of activities undertaken in assigned areas to the FT at the end of every working day.', 'Achieved', 'The figures I give from the field are always true and incase of anything might just be because of human error.', 'The employee has been honest with his work and errors which are detected after tree counting he always suggest and ready to do recounting to get the correct figure.', '2021-11-10 05:40:16', '2021-11-10 05:40:16'),
(132, 47, 'Farmers verification', 'Not Achieved', 'We had three categories of farmers and so far the first and second categories will be achieved by the end of November 2021.', 'The verification excercise on the right track and there has been improved data quality. More need to be done though to make sure field team dont provide wrong information and this can be achieved through constant checks and monitoring of their activities.', '2021-11-10 06:00:23', '2021-11-10 06:00:23'),
(133, 47, 'Farmer group trainings', 'Not Achieved', 'The objective was interrupted with farm reverification exercise.', 'Group activity is wanting and more emphasis knowing our groups, reactivation and formation', '2021-11-10 06:00:23', '2021-11-10 06:00:23'),
(134, 47, 'Contract issuing out', 'Not Achieved', '137 contracts were issued out   for those farmers whose coordinates were taken. Other farmers had no coordinates and correct details which were still taken during verification activity.', 'issuing of contract is key our farmers but having the correct information about our farmer is the most important so that the accurate details apperas on the contracts', '2021-11-10 06:00:23', '2021-11-10 06:00:23'),
(135, 47, 'Moringa management', 'Achieved', 'Continous managemnent through protection against pests, diseases and weeds and harvesting done.', 'this is a new exercise and much need to be done. we need to have work instruction for harvesting and storing moringa before end of November 2021', '2021-11-10 06:00:23', '2021-11-10 06:00:23'),
